The page edit restrictions function would benefit from a warning which warned if the user/group you are adding to the restricted list is unable to edit the page.  If the you attempt to add an edit restriction to a user that cannot edit the page to begin with, it should either deny the ability to add the restriction or at least warn that they do not have edit permission.

For example, if user 'Camel' is part of group 'Camelus' and this group does not have edit permissions to the space 'zoo' then adding a page restriction stating that only user 'Camel' can edit a page is pointless as the 'Camelus' group cannot edit any part of the space 'zoo'.

