I upgraded Confluence 3.5.13 to 4.1-rc1 with the automated installer. 

The existing {{bin/setenv.sh}} file contains the variable {{JAVA_OPTS}} that spans multiple lines:
{code}
JAVA_OPTS="-Xms256m -Xmx640m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m $JAVA_OPTS -Djava.awt.headless=true \
-Dupm.pac.disable=true "
export JAVA_OPTS
{code}

After the upgrade the new {{setenv.sh}} file is invalid because the second {{JAVA_OPTS}} line is missing and the quote character is escaped:
{code}
JAVA_OPTS="-Xms256m -Xmx640m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m $JAVA_OPTS -Djava.awt.headless=true \"
export JAVA_OPTS
{code}

This malformed file prevents a successful start of the new Confluence version.

